content: Turns out I simply don't know how to read, and applied to the openai beta instead of the gptf one. Sorry for bothering you. Have a great day.
Arthur Adjedj has marked this topic as resolved.

Arthur Adjedj said:

Hi, I tried setting up everything in order to use lean-gptf, but when trying to use the tactic, I end up with the following error message : 

[gptf_proof_search_step] run_best_beam_candidate UNEXPECTED MESSAGE:
---
["ERROR { \"error\":{ \"code\":null, \n    \"message\":\"No such organization: org-kuQ09yewcuHU5GN5YYEUp2hh.\", \n    \"param\":null, \n    \"type\":\"invalid_request_error\"}}"]
---

I tried changing the org name to my personal one, but it lead to a new error saying the engine doesn't exist since it should be tied to the other, first org. What can I do to correct this ? Thanks in advance for the help

I'm getting the exact same error with the same org id. How did you manage to resolve it? I also followed the same steps of ttps://github.com/jesse-michael-han/lean-gptf.
(By the way, i did not get an email with instruction as advertised on the google form ( https://bit.ly/3nNWMyB), but a direct email from Open AI. I have my API_KEY from https://beta.openai.com/account/api-keys.
I've experienced the Engine not found error and explicitly providing the key in the lean file solves that.
